  section
    h2 Situation Awareness
    blockquote(style='font-size: 140%;') The continuous extraction of environmental information along with integration of this information with previous knowledge to form a coherent mental picture, and the end use of that mental picture in directing further perception and anticipating future need.
    p(style='text-align: right; font-size: 65%;')
      | - Dominguez, et al, 1994
  section
    h2 Situation Awareness
    blockquote(style='font-size: 140%;') Knowing what is going on so you can figure out what to do.
    p(style='text-align: right; font-size: 65%;')
      | - Adam, 1983
  section
    h2 SA for Cyber Security
    ul
      li <strong>Design for scale</strong> - even on small networks, huge volumes of data from many different kinds of sensors
      li <strong>Process in real-time</strong> - an intruder can be there and gone by the time an attack is discovered
      li <strong>Integrate domain knowledge</strong> - analysts are extremely knowledgeable in their domain and in their environment
      li <strong>Provide context</strong> - analysts require contextual understanding of an event to make decisions
