  section
    h1 Stucco
    h3 Situation and Threat Understanding by Correlating Contextual Observations
    p
      img(src='img/stucco-thumb.png', style='border:none;')
  section
    h2 stucco :: problem
    ul
      li To make decisions about security events, analysts require <strong>context</strong>
      li Trigger events (e.g. IDS alerts) rarely include the much needed context
      li Analysts must manually locate, collect and synthesize relevant data from a variety of sources to construct a contextual understanding of an event
  section
    h2 stucco :: overview
    p(style='text-align:left;') Stucco will collect data sources not typically integrated into security systems and extract relevant data into a <strong>knowledge graph</strong> to accelerate situational understanding
  section
    h2 stucco :: philosophy
    ul
      li Users need <strong>information</strong> to gain situational understanding – not more data
        ul
          li Our focus is not simply collecting more data and indexing or clustering documents
          li Our focus is to organize domain concepts that match the way analysts think and facilitate understanding
      li Users need a place to store and retrieve <strong>their knowledge</strong>
        ul
          li Our focus is not just on retrieval, but on providing a space to collaborate on incidents
          li Our focus is on creating a knowledge graph that includes both domain and situated knowledge
  section
